HEADWORD: Nausea
<hw>Nau"se*a</hw> <pr>(? or <?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<?/, fr. <grk>nay^s</grk> ship. See <er>Nave</er> of a church, and cf.
<er>Noise</er>.]</ety> <def>Seasickness; hence, any similar sickness of
the stomach accompanied with a propensity to vomit; qualm; squeamishness
of the stomach; loathing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nauseant</ent>⟦br⟧
